        "content": "<p>When introducing variables, is there a way to keep the orignal without loosing it? I vaguely recall someone addressing this. when i consult Gemini it hallucinates up something using the @ symbol, the following: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- Retain 'h' as the whole proof of (A ∧ B),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- and break it into 'ha' and 'hb'</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rintro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"bp\">@⟨</span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- Context now has:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- h : A ∧ B</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- ha : A</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- hb : B</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- (dummy proof to finish)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>However it doesn't work with error:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`introN</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failed</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">There</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">are</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">no</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">additional</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">binders</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`let</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">goal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">introduce</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span>\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CLean</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is there a way to do this? Any help would be appreciated <span aria-label=\"smiley\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f603\" role=\"img\" title=\"smiley\">:smiley:</span></p>",
